<br>
AO &quot;hard caps&quot; player attack speed at 1.0 seconds attack and 1.0 seconds recharge no matter what weapon.  At full aggressive (agg/def slider) you only need ~150 Phys Init to use pure fists at full speed, and only ~300 Phys Init to use fists+claw at full speed.  All of your &quot;extra&quot; Phys Init will NOT allow you to attack faster than 1s Attack/1s Recharge, but it WILL allow you to lower your agg/def bar and assume a more defensive posture (take more advantage of your evades) and still hit at full speed.  Check that FAQ again for more details.<br>
<br>
Somewhere around the &quot;low 110s-120s&quot; you will be better off dropping your claw and going to pure fists, since your claw attack rating will really start lagging far behind your fist attack rating.  And since attack rating has a large impact on your chance to crit, you will eventually reach a break point where the extra damage from your increased fist criticals actually outweighs the increased number of attacks gained from using the claw.  Since all of this depends on where you have spent your IP and what your implants and equipment are like, there is no solid level threshhold I can give you.  Just do what Maxius did: sometime between 110 and 140, try some fights with and without the claw and note the damage and # of crits...if you can't discern a difference there is not much reason to change...once you CAN tell a difference in your crits/damage-over-time it's time to stop using your claw. (There are even some 3rd party damage tracking utilities out there now that can help you make this assessment.)<br>
<br>
If you are nearing level 70 as an MA, your next major goal should be to get into Q125 implants ASAP, and start hoarding/spending IP so that you can self-buff Vulnerability Seeker.  If you are VERY aggressive with IP and implants, you can self-buff V Seeker at level 74.  Less obsessive MAs can get VS by level 80 without much trouble.  But no matter what your pace, V Seeker is your next milestone..the sooner you reach it, the better. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
