AODD simply adds up all of the damage that is done by you or anyone who's name you enter into it and spit out a total. It does not care what level you are, what level the monster is or what weapons, if any, you are using, and spits it out the total when you tell it to. So, what you will have to do is go find 2 mobs that you can fight one at a time, that are the same level and type(mutant camp?) and check the total for each fight. I would suggest multiple trials before I made a decision.<br>
AODD cannot attach nano damage to the dealer because AODD gets its info from the chat text. Chat text does not specify who did the nano damage so it just counts all nano damage done to any enemy. This is also tracked seperately from all other damage types. If you are using MA attacks instead of weapons, you should definetly add this in to get a true reading of how much each setup did for damage. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/bio/d/1/name/viirruss">Viirruss</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
